 To adjust the sensor sensitivity for a Texas Instruments SensorTag, you would need to use the SensorTag's API and the appropriate configuration settings. The SensorTag has several sensors on board, including an accelerometer, gyroscope, magnetometer, temperature sensor, and humidity sensor.

For example, to adjust the sensitivity of the accelerometer sensor, you can use the `SensorHub` API provided by the SensorTag. Here's an example code snippet in C:
```c
// Initialize the sensor hub
sensorHub = SensorHub_open();

// Set the accelerometer sensitivity
status = SensorHub_setAccelerometerSensitivity(sensorHub, 16); // Set to 16 G for a range of +-2 g

// Close the sensor hub
SensorHub_close(sensorHub);
```
In this example, we're setting the accelerometer sensitivity to 16 G, which corresponds to a range of +-2 g. Other available sensitivity values are 8 G (range of +-4 g) and 4 G (range of +-8 g).

Similarly, you can use the `SensorHub` API to adjust the sensitivity of other sensors on board as well. Note that the specific configuration settings may vary depending on the sensor being used.

It's also worth noting that the SensorTag has a limited number of pins available for external connections, so you may need to carefully plan your circuit layout to avoid conflicts with other components or the SensorTag's built-in sensors.
